<TITLE> Court orders deportation of Sabbir murder suspect from UK </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 9 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka court Monday gave permission to bring back Shafiyat Sobhan Sanbir from the UK, with the help of the Interpol, to question him over the killing of Basundhara Group director Humayun Kabir Sabbir. Sabbir's body was recovered from a house owned by Basundhara Group in Gulshan on July 6 last year. CID assistant police super Arman Ali, assigned to investigate the case, appealed to court to bring back the son of Basundhara Group chairman Ahmed Akbar Sobhan from London for questioning. Magistrate Md Shamsul Alam of Dhaka Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court approved the appeal. The magistrate took recorded statements from two 'entertainers', Papiya Gain Papri and Sumi Akter Ratri. Sabbir's brother-in-law AFM Asif filed the murder case without naming an accused. The case alleged some unknown persons took Sabbir in a car from in front the house on the night of July 6, 2006. Sabbir was later found dead. In the first information report, it was also mentioned that Sabbir was thrown from the roof of the house. The case record shows that two persons named Khairul Hasan Ujjal and Shamsuddin Ahmed were arrested, taken into remand and interrogated in connection with the case. The case documents also show Shafiyat surrendered to the High Court on Nov 22 last year, but the High Court ordered him not to be arrested or harassed. bdnews24.c
